column5: any one know how kemplephelt bay is for smallies and or pike or lakers? i will be fishing out of a canoe for the one last time out? thanks darryl also what would some good baits be thanks bigredfisher
well lakers have been closed for over a month, so I wouldn't go after them  smallies are being caught lots out from the tiffin launch pike I don't know
I don't think there are pike in kempenfelt, the bulk are all in cook's bay.  Kemp is however loaded with fat perch right now.
Think again fella.  There's lots of big pike in Kempenfelt, caught them up to 41 inches.
Schaweet, I didn't know that (nice pic ).  I guess everyone always just names Cook's as the pike spot.  I gotta give kempenfelt a try then.
I have caught several pike in Kempenfelt including some nice 30+ inchers
ive caught plenty of pike over 10 lbs in kempenfelt when the perch are in. and ive seen some big pike come through the ice aswell!!!!
